        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl0_Label1"><p>Windows Server 2019 is now available for everyone and many companies are planning the migration to the new operating system to benefit from the new features. The thrust of the new Windows Server 2019 has been focused on hybrid cloud environments and the virtualization is the hearth of everything. Hyper-V 2019 introduces new features to [&hellip;]</p>
